        "created_at": "2021-10-26T08:15:41.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Very tight on pouring, showing a touch of coal smoke and a bare suggestion of red fruits. After taking on air it really gets going. There are rose petals and floral spice. The red fruits gather and intensify at the wine\u2019s core. It is lacy and there\u2019s a fine line of minerally acidity. It possesses latent power and really fans out on the long finish.</p>",
